"Across the 2010 through 2019 seasons, which constructor was the most competitive in qualifying, measured by the smallest typical gap to pole position? For each race, take pole as the fastest single-session qualifying time of any driver, and take each constructor's gap as its best driver's best time minus pole. Average that gap within each season first, then average those season figures across the decade so that seasons with more races do not dominate. Consider only constructors with a season figure in at least 8 of the 10 seasons. Return the constructor name and the resulting mean gap in seconds."
